<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading">12. Board Gaming</h3>



<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Although the limitation to board gamin=
g is that it=E2=80=99s a social hobby for the most part, it otherwise offer=
s a whole lot of variation to what type of games you can play. For example,=
 knowledge-based games like Trivial Pursuit, roleplaying games like Dungeon=
s &amp; Dragons, and so on. Board games are also most certainly not made so=
lely for kids but can be entirely enjoyable among a group of adults, too.&n=
bsp; If you don=E2=80=99t know where to start, check out our </span><a href=
=3D"https://bucketlistjourney.net/board-game-bucket-list/">Board Games Buck=
et List</a> that has 50 of the all time best ones to play.</p>



